# MiladyOS file_contexts.
#
# Vendor file_contexts entries merge into the device's vendor_file_contexts
# at build time (see BOARD_VENDOR_SEPOLICY_DIRS in milady_common.mk).
#
# Paths under /data/data/<pkg>/ are NOT labeled by file_contexts at install
# time — installd labels them via seapp_contexts (priv-apps land on
# `privapp_data_file`). The labels below take effect only when the agent
# service explicitly invokes restorecon(8) / SELinux.restoreconRecursive on
# the agent runtime dir after copying the bun binary out of assets/. See
# Phase B (MiladyAgentService) and the README in this directory.
#
# These two patterns separate the agent runtime files into:
#   1. Executables (bun, ld-musl, libstdc++, libgcc_s) — labeled
#      `milady_agent_exec`. Used as the entrypoint that triggers the
#      domain transition from priv_app -> milady_agent.
#   2. Everything else under the agent dir — labeled `milady_agent_data`
#      (writable scratch the child process owns).
#
# The order matters: more specific patterns (the bin subdirectory) come
# first so they win over the broader catch-all rule.
/data/data/com\.miladyai\.milady/files/agent/bin(/.*)?       u:object_r:milady_agent_exec:s0
/data/data/com\.miladyai\.milady/files/agent(/.*)?           u:object_r:milady_agent_data:s0
